<h1>Remove single-cell pits</h1>

<p>This tool can be used to remove single-grid-cell pits, or topographic
depressions. These are grid cells in digital elevation models (DEMs) that have
no neighbouring cells with a lower or equal elevation. The algorithm will raise
the elevation of pit cells to the level of the lowest neighbour plus a small
elevation value (0.0001). The user must specify the names of the input DEM and
the output image. Larger-sized depressions can be removed with either <a
href="FillDeps.html">depression filling</a> or <a href="BreachDeps.html">depression breaching</a>.</p>
<br>


